<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>827</anchor> <rss>2023-09-29.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Entry</taxon> <addr>2023-09-29</addr>  <route>2023-09-29.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>2023-09-29</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter/> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related/> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>828</anchor> <rss>2023-09-28.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Entry</taxon> <addr>2023-09-28</addr>  <route>2023-09-28.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>28</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>2023-09-28</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>I have added an informal <link href="jms-009R.xml" type="local" title="I am hiring!">job posting</link> to my home page in regard to the newly awarded <link href="jms-008K.xml" type="local" title="New spaces for denotational semantics">new spaces for denotational semantics</link> grant. I have also sent my final revision of <link href="sterling-2023-grothendieck.xml" type="local" title="Towards a geometry for syntax">towards a geometry for syntax</link> to the editor of the <link href="chapman-grothendieck-2022.xml" type="local" title="Grothendieck Conference">Grothendieck Conference</link> proceedings.</p><p>I received all my new office equipment and have mostly set it up; will bring a mechanical keyboard from home <link href="2023-09-29.xml" type="local" title="2023-09-29">tomorrow</link>. I am using the new equipment to give my <link href="sterling-2023-topos-colloquium.xml" type="local" title="Synthetic domains in the 21st century">topos colloquium</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>